<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written Evidence submitted by the Newcastle University Universities and Colleges Union (WSC037)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written Evidence submitted by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Newcastle University </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Universities and Colleges Union (WSC037)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Introduction</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This document suggests that a barrier to the careers of women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in science in academia is the lack of long term funding leading to a lack of security of employment.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The prospect of constantly looking for their next funded appointment is daunting to many women especially those trying to combine a career with raising a f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">amily. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  In addition that the short term nature of research employment in academia leads to a lack of responsibility being </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">shown by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">leaders of research for researchers’ career development </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which is detrimental to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> long term career prospects. It suggests ways</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in which the funding providers could address these issues. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If one accepts that the bulk of many people’s university careers will continue to depend on short to medium term funding from research councils and their like and that there are many pressures o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n people, particularly women, which prevent them from moving from establishment to establishment to keep in work then the responsibility for helping them to establish a career and remain in work has to come from the academics who are leading research and t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he funders who fund them.  One also has to accept that the once expected career path of moving from post- doctoral researcher to an academic role is not feasible in the current financial climate.  Universities are unlikely to ever undertake to employ as te</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nured academics, the numbers of people who are needed to carry out the amount of research that needs doing and that somebody can have a career as a researcher needs to be accepted by academics.  It then follows that the academics’ responsibilities to peopl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e who work in this way need to be reinforced by their employers and regarded as a serious responsibility and a fundamental part of their academic role. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A fundamental way of addressing the problems of the appropriate funding/career development/ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">management</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of all staff would be for funders to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">report on the staff aspects of the research project as part of the milestones of the project and for the funders to hold the CIs/PIs accountable for the future development of the people employed on research projects le</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d by them.  Responsibility for ensuring accountability should be given to a named CI/PI where there is more than one, or to a named person in each institution/organisational unit where there is collaboration. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Responsibilities would include: </span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a requiremen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t to inform the funder of the names and job titles of the people</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> funded by the research project</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a requirement to provide summaries at key milestones showing that regular (bi-annual?) discussions about, future careers, training and what will happen at the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">end of the project have taken place  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A requirement to provide a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">document </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">signed by all parties</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">confirming that the above discussion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> have taken place</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Individual forms from staff members recording their comments on their management during the course of the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> project</span></li></ul><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The funders should require that universities have proven policies on internal redeployment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">and evidenced</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">of their effectiveness</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and career management for researchers. Specific </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">questions on turnover of staff and their reasons for leaving could be a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sked for by all funding bodies, preferably staff should be asked to confirm their reasons for leaving an institution.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A decision to remain as a contract researcher without desire for promotion should be acceptable to all parties since these people are ofte</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n extremely experienced and very competent in the roles in which they choose to work. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A proportion of the funding should be withheld if expected milestones in this area are not met, (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as they would for any other part of the project that was not competed to the funders’ satisfaction).</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Milestones could include</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Ensuring ar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rangements </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">redeployment of staff either within the university or within the existing unit at the end of the pro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ject </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Providing bridging between projects – time can be spent writing papers, doing training or writing bids under guidance </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Appropriate time </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">being </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">given to training and development </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">by timetabling it into activities or proving attendance at appropriate tra</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ining courses </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">– funders need to recognise this need in their funding models</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A statement of how CIs/PIs will demonstrate good practice </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should also form part of the award process – though without </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">follow up on how this was implemented will be essential</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In ad</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">dition to all of this, funders need to be explicit in their requirements that CIs/PIs insist that staff have a good work/life balance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> appropriate recognition of family and other responsibilities and to insist on other arrangements that will make life for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women at work easier </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are implemented </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">– holding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">meetings</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> at sensible times is only one of a series of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">behaviours </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">encourage women to feel that they can be successful and happy at work. All people participating on the project should be given a docu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ment which outlines the CIs/PIs expectations (based on the funder’s expectations and requirements) and they should be encouraged to report poor management and behaviour to the funding body anonymously if necessary.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Formalising the need for staff management in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">way </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that would affect the research income of those who do not reach a good standard of support for staff </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">would </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ensure that all employers and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">-Investigators/Principal Investigators </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">become tuned into the n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eeds of the people they employ and make careers in science more acceptable to women. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>